      In our experiment, in order to produce benzyl alcohol, we need to take Phenylpyruvate as the initial metabolite and produce benzyl alcohol through a series of enzymatic reactions.So we need to add the reaction that produces benzyl alcohol to our model.

      In our experiment, in order to produce benzyl alcohol, we need to take Phenylpyruvate as the initial metabolite and produce benzyl alcohol through a series of enzymatic reactions.So we need to add the reaction that produces benzyl alcohol to our model.

      In [78]:
       
      def ranking(opt1, opt2, model1, model2):
          scores = []
          for r in model1.reactions:
              s = opt2.fluxes[r.id]-opt1.fluxes[r.id]
              scores.append([r.id, s])
          print(len(scores))
          return scores
      . . .
